title: Sidewall, 1796–1800
creditline: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
description: Vertical rectangle. Repeating pattern of squares containing alternately a circle enclosing a seated figure holding a parasol, and four intersecting arcs enclosing urns and foliage. The large squares are separated by simple meander bands set with conventionalized tulips.

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, 1796–1800.
1796–1800. Block-printed on handmade paper. Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt. 1931-45-11.
